title: Molitor - 2014 - #lonelypeople_Music [FLAC]
description:
"Growing up in a city known simultaneously as the honeymoon and suicide capital of the world; Niagara Falls, Ontario stuffed Molitor full of capitalism and flashing lights at an early age.

At only 20, Molitor combines ambient guitar riffs with dark, pumping beats and hypnotic vocals that will rip into you with nostalgia. A perfect marriage between modern Hip-Hop/R&B and 1980's new wave with dance-y Indie-Pop as the ring.

Currently in the studio working on his debut full-length album with Grammy award-nominated producers, musicians and engineers that have worked with Imagine Dragons, The Killers, Vampire Weekend, Walk the Moon and many more."
